Package: NilpotentMinimum
Type: Package
Title: Basic R Functionality for (Strong and Weak) Nilpotent Minimum fuzzy logics
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(
      "Igor", "Yegin",
      email = "igor.yegin@stir.ac.uk",
      role = c("aut", "cre")
    )
  )
Description: (Strong) Nilpotent Minimum (commonly shortened to NM) is a class of t-norms 
    introduced by Fodor (1995) and later generalised as Weak Nilpotent Minimum (WNM) by 
    Esteva and Godo (2001). This package provides a number of R functions for NM logic 
    whose syntax is similar to that of lfl package. 
    However, unlike lfl, NilpotentMininum is written entirely in native R code.
